{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_oliver_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280600556/1930111601/0113.xml":{"full_text":"A-16\nREALTY SWINDLE\nCHARGED TO TWO\nShortage of Over $120,000\nAdmitted; Embezzling De\nnied by Couple.\nMr the Associated Press.\nPHILADELPHIA, November 15. \u2014Two\nreal estate operators from Chicago, a\nman and a woman, were arrested here\ntoday accused of embezzling -several\nhundred thousand dollars of clients\u2019\nmoney.\nThey are John Naughton, 40, and\nMrs. Hilda X. Schroeder, 48.\nAdmitting they came here because\ntheir Chicago business failed, both said\nthe total shortage charged to them\nwould amount to between $120,000 and\n$150,000. Both denied embezzlement.\n\u201cOur trouble was due solely to the\nslump in real estate and the general\nbusiness depression,\u2019\u2019 Mrs. Bchroeder\nsaid, according to detectives. \u201cThere\nwas nothing criminal in our conduct.\nWe didn't steal anybody's money: we\nsimply failed. I am willing to go back\nand face the music.\u201d\nThe two were traced through a ship\nment of clothing sent by express to\nMrs. Schroeder by a daughter living in\nMilwaukee.\nDetectives arrested Mrs. Schroeder in\nher apartment. A 15-year-old son liv\ning with her is being cared for by the\npolice pending disposition of her case.\nMTs. Schroeder said Naughton was\nemployed in a real estate office near\nTenth and Spruce streets. They went\nthere and arrested him.\nALUMNI OF BIG TEN\nTO MEET SATURDAY\nEntertainment Program Arranged\nfor Former Students at Tenth\nAnnual Bound-Up.\nAlumni of universities in the Big Ten\nConference will gather in reunion Sat\nurday night at the tenth annual Big\nTen round-up at the Washington Hotel.\nKarl Hoffman, alumnus of lowa Uni\nversity, who has charge of arrange\nments, has issued Invitations to all\nstudents formerly enrolled in the \u201cBig\nTen.\"\nThe program will be strictly one of\nentertainment, reunion groups, vaude\nville sketches and a dance having been\narranged. The round-up will also con\nsider the final standing of the Big Ten\nfoot ball teams, the Western Confer\nence inter-school schedule being con\ncluded Saturday afternoon.\nTickets may be procured from E.\nMark Ferree of the Publicity Commit\ntee. 3820 Sixteenth street.\nLearn the Art of\nDramatizing the Table\nFour Well Known Washington\nWomen's Clubs Participate. in\nA TABLE-SETTING\nCOMPETITION\n11\nTuesday, November 18, at 3 P.M.\nThe tables will be set for formal dinners, luncheons\nand buffet supper. The contestants will choose all\nchina, glass, silver and linen from Lansburgh\u2019s regular\nstocks. The winning club will be presented with a ster\nling silver flower bowl. Everyone is cordially invited\nto see the tables and be present during the judging.\nThe Contestants The Judges\nIndude the M\u2122 Caroline Duer\nWomen\u2019s City Club of the Vogue staff and\nGeorgetown Garden Club an international au-\nHousekeepers\u2019 Alliance tbority on table setting.\n\u2022<i Park View Women\u2019s Club Mrs. Luther D. Reichel\n-5 dcffff, Washington,\nThe tables will remain on _ ___\n<&pUy m the Chrna Secfon Director of Netiona!\nall week. Come in to see School of Fine and\nthem l Applied Art.\ni\nv -j, I, i\nThe Judging Will take place Tuesday afternoon, h.\n3 o\u2019clock in die China Department on the Sixth Floor.\nFollowing the Contest Miss Caroline Duer will\nspeak on modem table setting as one finds it in correct\nly smart homes today.\n4\nLaNSBURCH'S\n7th, Bth and E Sts.\u2014NAtional 9800\nHo Connection With Any Other Washington Store\n4 11 1\n\nLANSBURCH'S\n7th, Bth and E Sts.\u2014NAtional 9800\nNo Connection With Any Other Washington Store\nSkPlSl Evvry Day During November Wa\u2019ra Bajp-fe,,\npv Faaturiag an Extraordinary Valna ia\nToy town\u2014Watch for Thaml\nigX/-- \u2014I can go to sleep, I have real\nhair and beautiful eyelashes. gj\nYou\u2019ll adore my smocked and em\nbroidered dress and bonnet. I\u2019m\nTOYTOWN\u2014FOURTH FLOOB\nTHE SUNDAY STAB, WASHINGTON, D. C